\begin{align*}
\text{Average} &= \frac{\frac{2}{3} + \frac{4}{5}}{2}\\
&= \frac{\frac{10}{15} + \frac{12}{15}}{2}\\
&= \frac{\frac{22}{15}}{2}\\
&= \frac{22}{15} / 2\\
&= \frac{22}{30}\\
&= \frac{11}{15}
\end{align*}
The common fraction exactly half-way between $\frac{2}{3}$ and $\frac{4}{5}$ is $\frac{11}{15}$.

